<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="50" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,1264,1613]" pageId="11" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1264,1289]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" reason="1">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species is close to 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Inoue" authorityYear="1956" baseAuthorityName="Leech" baseAuthorityYear="1888" box="[555,659,1265,1288]" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Tridrepana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crocea">
<emphasis box="[555,659,1265,1288]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="50">T. crocea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on both external and male genitalic features. But in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chu &amp; Wang" authorityYear="1988" box="[1265,1386,1264,1288]" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Tridrepana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hainana">
<emphasis box="[1265,1386,1264,1288]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="50">T. hainana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the socii are longer; the dorsal part of the gnathos is much broader and concave medially, with long hairs, while it is semicircular with short spines in 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Inoue" authorityYear="1956" baseAuthorityName="Leech" baseAuthorityYear="1888" box="[528,631,1337,1360]" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Tridrepana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crocea">
<emphasis box="[528,631,1337,1360]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="50">T. crocea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; the anellus is slender, with the basal branches thinner and less sclerotized than in 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Inoue" authorityYear="1956" baseAuthorityName="Leech" baseAuthorityYear="1888" box="[297,399,1373,1396]" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Tridrepana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crocea">
<emphasis box="[297,399,1373,1396]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="50">T. crocea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the middle of the anellus bears an acute process, and the end of the anellus has a pair of triangular processes, both of them pointed ventrally; the posterior margin of the eighth tergite is concave and with two pointed tines in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chu &amp; Wang" authorityYear="1988" box="[383,503,1444,1468]" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Tridrepana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hainana">
<emphasis box="[383,503,1444,1468]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="50">T. hainana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but rounded in 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Inoue" authorityYear="1956" baseAuthorityName="Leech" baseAuthorityYear="1888" box="[690,793,1445,1468]" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Tridrepana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crocea">
<emphasis box="[690,793,1445,1468]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="50">T. crocea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; the posterior margin of the eighth sternite is round in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chu &amp; Wang" authorityYear="1988" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Tridrepana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hainana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="50">T. hainana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but bell-like and concave in 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Inoue" authorityYear="1956" baseAuthorityName="Leech" baseAuthorityYear="1888" box="[567,670,1481,1504]" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Tridrepana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crocea">
<emphasis box="[567,670,1481,1504]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="50">T. crocea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
